iane\"","Artist":"Abraham Bosse after Claude Vignon","Date":"published 1639","Medium":"etching and engraving","CreditLine":"Ailsa Mellon Bruce Fund","URL":"https://www.nga.gov/artworks/60810","ImageURL":"https://api.nga.gov/iiif/8677ad1c-95e3-4fe4-9932-113a66ad73a4/full/!800,800/0/default.jpg"},{"ObjectID":62966,"Title":"Water and Earth/Autumn and Winter","Artist":"Swiss 16th Century","Date":"late 16th century","Medium":"pen and black ink with gray wash","CreditLine":"Julius S. Held Collection","URL":"https://www.nga.gov/artworks/62966","ImageURL":"https://api.nga.gov/iiif/bccd9124-ac28-407b-8189-1b086f58ade2/full/!800,800/0/default.jpg"},{"ObjectID":67817,"Title":"Embarkation at Genoa","Artist":"Jacques Callot","Date":"1612","Medium":"etching on laid paper [restrike]","CreditLine":"Transferred from The Library of Congress","URL":"https://www.nga.gov/artworks/67817","ImageURL":"https://api.nga.gov/iiif/ffe85066-13ea-4f93-90ff-71b0b0e0f46d/full/!800,800/0/default.jpg"},{"ObjectID":69973,"Title":"Village along a River Estuary in Devon","Artist":"Thomas Girtin","Date":"1797/1798","Medium":"watercolor over graphite on oatmeal paper","CreditLine":"Gift of The Circle of the National Gallery of Art","URL":"https://www.nga.gov/artworks/69973","ImageURL":"https://api.nga.gov/iiif/721165f3-6339-4011-b9a8-91fc2a8ba849/full/!800,800/0/default.jpg"},{"ObjectID":71590,"Title":"Mountain Landscape with Washerwomen and a Fisherman","Artist":"Francesco Zuccarelli","Date":"1762/1765","Medium":"gouache over black chalk (laid on modern paper)","CreditLine":"Gift of John Morton Morris, in Honor of the 50th Anniversary of the National Gallery of Art","URL":"https://www.nga.gov/artworks/71590","ImageURL":"https://api.nga.gov/iiif/5e3ec63f-20c6-4eb9-982b-71a591003da3/full/!800,800/0/default.jpg"},{"ObjectID":73746,"Title":"Raffaello Menicucci","Artist":"Claude Mellan","Date":"","Medium":"engraving on laid paper","CreditLine":"Gift of John O'Brien","URL":"https://www.nga.gov/artworks/73746",